Enclosing class:
MultiDiskBTree
public class MultiDiskBTree.Level1IndexEntry
extends ORTree.IndexEntry

This class describes the index entries for level 1 (i.e. the entries of the non-leaf nodes with level=1) of a MultiDiskBTree. Each index entry refers to a node which is the root of the subtree. We call this node the subnode of the index entry.

See Also:
ORTree.IndexEntry, MultiDiskBTree.Level2IndexEntry

initialize

public Tree.IndexEntry initialize(Container container,

Description copied from class: Tree.IndexEntry
Initializes the (new created) IndexEntry. The default implementation only calls the method Tree.IndexEntry.initialize(Object id).

Overrides:
initialize in class Tree.IndexEntry
Parameters:
container - the container in which the Node referred to by the IndexEntry is stored. In the default implementation the container is ignored because it is determined by Tree.getContainer.
id - the ID (in the underlaying container) of the Node refered to by the IndexEntry
Returns:
the IndexEntry itself (i.e. return this).
